      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Antislot Legal</p>
          <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            This policy explains what data Antislot collects, why we collect
            it, how it's stored and protected, and the rights you have over
            your information.
          </p>
          <p class="lead">
            <strong>Effective date:</strong> May 15, 2026 &middot;
            <strong>Last updated:</strong> May 15, 2026
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Antislot ("we", "us", "our") is a self-help mobile application that
        supports people building healthier habits around gambling urges. The
        app is published on the Apple App Store and Google Play and is
        operated by an independent developer based in Türkiye.
      </p>
      <p>
        For any privacy question, request, or complaint, contact us at
        <a class="contact-mail" href="mailto:support@antislot.app">support@antislot.app</a>.
        We act as the data controller for the limited information described
        below.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">2. Our privacy principles</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>On-device by default.</strong> Your recovery progress, journal entries, urge logs, and personal preferences are stored on your device — not on our servers.</li>
        <li><strong>No advertising.</strong> Antislot contains no third-party advertising and we do not sell or rent your data.</li>
        <li><strong>No behavioral tracking.</strong> We do not use cross-app tracking identifiers and we do not request the App Tracking Transparency permission.</li>
        <li><strong>Account-free.</strong> Antislot does not require you to create an account or provide your real name to use the core app.</li>
        <li><strong>Minimum necessary data.</strong> We only collect what we need to provide the feature you are using.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">3. Data we process</h2>

      <h3 class="card-title">3.1 Stored on your device only</h3>
      <p>
        The following are written to your device's secure storage
        (<code>expo-secure-store</code> / Keychain on iOS, EncryptedSharedPreferences
        on Android) and never leave your device unless you explicitly export them:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Recovery progress, streak counters, and milestone history.</li>
        <li>Urge logs, mood / craving check-ins, and journal entries you create.</li>
        <li>Mindfulness session history and personal goals.</li>
        <li>App preferences (theme, language, notification settings, opt-in toggles).</li>
        <li>Premium subscription state (whether your subscription is currently active).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="card-title">3.2 Processed by our servers</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>AI coaching messages.</strong> When you send a message in the
          in-app AI chat, the most recent messages of that conversation are sent
          to our backend (<code>api.antislot.app</code>) and forwarded to the
          underlying AI provider (OpenAI or Google Gemini) so a reply can be
          generated. We do not require your name or contact details to use this
          feature; we recommend not including identifying personal information
          in your messages. Messages are not used to train AI models.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Premium purchase receipts.</strong> When you buy or restore an
          Antislot Premium subscription, the signed App Store receipt
          (StoreKit 2 JWS) is sent to our backend so we can cryptographically
          verify it against Apple's certificate chain and activate your
          subscription. We store only the transaction identifier for
          duplicate-protection purposes; we do not receive your payment card
          details, name, or email — those stay with Apple.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Operational logs.</strong> Our servers keep short-lived
          request logs (timestamp, endpoint, response status, truncated IP)
          for up to 30 days for security, abuse prevention, and debugging.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="card-title">3.3 Optional diagnostics</h3>
      <p>
        If you enable diagnostics from in-app settings, anonymized crash
        reports and performance traces are sent to Sentry. These reports
        contain device model, OS version, app version, and a stack trace; they
        do not include your journal entries, AI messages, or other personal
        content. Diagnostics are off by default for end users and can be
        toggled off at any time.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">4. Why we process this data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>To provide the app's features</strong> (recovery tracking, urge logging, AI coaching, subscription unlocks). Legal basis: performance of a contract / legitimate interest.</li>
        <li><strong>To validate purchases</strong> and protect against duplicate or fraudulent activations. Legal basis: legitimate interest, contractual necessity.</li>
        <li><strong>To keep the service secure and reliable</strong> (rate-limiting, abuse prevention, debugging). Legal basis: legitimate interest.</li>
        <li><strong>To respond to your requests and legal obligations</strong> (support, deletion, regulatory compliance). Legal basis: legal obligation / consent.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">5. Sharing &amp; sub-processors</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal data. We share limited information with
        the following service providers strictly to operate the app:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> and/or <strong>Google (Gemini API)</strong> — to generate AI coaching replies. Subject to their respective enterprise privacy terms; messages are not used for model training.</li>
        <li><strong>Apple Inc.</strong> — for App Store payments, subscription billing, and receipt validation. All payment data stays with Apple.</li>
        <li><strong>Google LLC</strong> — for Google Play payments where the Android app is distributed.</li>
        <li><strong>Sentry</strong> — only if you have opted in to diagnostic reporting.</li>
        <li><strong>Hosting provider (Vercel / our cloud provider)</strong> — for serving this website and our API endpoints.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We may also disclose information when required to do so by applicable
        law, court order, or to protect the rights, safety, and property of
        Antislot, our users, or the public.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">6. International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Some of our sub-processors (OpenAI, Google, Apple, Sentry) are located
        in or process data in the United States and other jurisdictions. Where
        your information is transferred outside Türkiye, the EEA, or the UK,
        we rely on standard contractual clauses or equivalent safeguards
        offered by those vendors.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">7. Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>On-device data:</strong> retained as long as the app is installed; you can clear it at any time from in-app settings or by uninstalling the app.</li>
        <li><strong>AI chat messages:</strong> processed in transit; we do not persist conversation history on our servers beyond what is needed to generate a reply.</li>
        <li><strong>Purchase / transaction records:</strong> retained for the lifetime of the subscription plus the period required to meet legal, tax, and accounting obligations.</li>
        <li><strong>Operational logs:</strong> typically up to 30 days.</li>
        <li><strong>Diagnostic reports (opt-in):</strong> retained per Sentry's default retention (typically 30–90 days).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct,
        export, or delete your personal data, to object to or restrict certain
        processing, and to withdraw consent. Türkiye residents have the rights
        described in Article 11 of the KVKK; EEA / UK residents have the
        rights described in Articles 15–22 of the GDPR.
      </p>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, email
        <a class="contact-mail" href="mailto:support@antislot.app">support@antislot.app</a>.
        We respond to verified requests within 30 days. You also have the right
        to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority (in
        Türkiye, the KVKK; in the EEA, your national supervisory authority).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">9. Children</h2>
      <p>
        Antislot is not directed to children. The app is intended for users
        who are at least 18 years old (or the age of legal majority in their
        jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal data from
        children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data,
        please contact us and we will delete it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">10. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use industry-standard safeguards to protect your information,
        including TLS for data in transit, secure platform key stores
        (Keychain / EncryptedSharedPreferences) for on-device data, signed
        receipt verification for purchases, and access controls on our
        backend. No internet service can be guaranteed 100% secure, but we
        review and update our security practices on an ongoing basis.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">11. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make
        material changes, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top
        of this page and, where appropriate, notify you in the app. Continued
        use of Antislot after the changes take effect constitutes acceptance
        of the revised policy.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card glass">
      <h2 class="card-title">12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, data subject requests, or any concerns about
        how Antislot handles your information:
      </p>
      <p>
        <a class="contact-mail" href="mailto:support@antislot.app">support@antislot.app</a>
      </p>
    </section>

